Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.26,0:00:06.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“You must not leave the harbor on the tenth of any month.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.68,0:00:09.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such was the rule at this port.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.06,0:00:23.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, never having heard of the rule,\Nseveral young fishermen took a boat out.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.41,0:00:26.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The boat swayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.16,0:00:28.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sky began to grow dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.49,0:00:31.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A strange fog enveloped them!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.67,0:00:36.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“My goodness, what could that be?”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.67,0:00:40.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A ghost ship appeared before them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.76,0:00:48.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A ghost ship so called because of the ghost controlling\Nit - the spirit of a sailor lost at sea on a stromy night.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.18,0:00:52.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ghost turned to the men, and said in a haunting voice:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.11,0:00:58.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,“Give me your ladle,”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.65,0:01:02.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,referring to the long-handled dipper the men carried.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.61,0:01:07.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not knowing what would happen if they refused its request,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.37,0:01:11.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,they handed the hapless ladle over to the ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.00,0:01:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Having appeased the ghost, the—
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.71,0:01:15.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Oh! Me! I know what happens!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.58,0:01:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It fills the ladle with sea water,\Nand the fishing boat sinks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.34,0:01:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, so it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.18,0:01:31.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, that is why a ship\Nshould always carry an extra ladle with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.60,0:01:35.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well done, Genyousai-sama! A wonderful tale!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.06,0:01:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, not at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.65,0:01:38.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well then,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.36,0:01:42.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,though we are all strangers, our fortunes have\Ncompelled us to travel on this same boat today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.15,0:01:48.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I may be so rude as to request it,\Nperhaps we should all introduce ourselves?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.12,0:01:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll go first, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.70,0:01:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Mikuniya Tamon.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.25,0:01:59.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I use this ship, the Sorarisu-maru, a former Shogunate\Nmerchant vessel, to bring curiosities from the West into Edo.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.42,0:02:02.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m just a simple merchant.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.80,0:02:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Yanagi Genyousai. As you can see, I am a minstrel.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.68,0:02:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I travel the world, telling of…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.89,0:02:13.27,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do I have to introduce myself to these old men?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.27,0:02:14.90,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(640,615,640,690,200,0)\t(50,200,\c&HE9ECF1&\3c&H262B32&)}Why do I have to introduce myself to these old men?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.89,0:02:16.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about you, young miss?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.85,0:02:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I’m Kayo.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.31,0:02:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be a seamstress in the Sakai house, but—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.99,0:02:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, do you mean the Sakai house of Ghost Cat fame?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.74,0:02:30.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, so that’s a famous story now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.33,0:02:32.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, yes, that’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.16,0:02:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve decided to go to Edo to find a new job, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.67,0:02:44.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And, um, Mr. Samurai, if you\Nwould honor us with your name…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.63,0:02:47.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sasaki Hyouei.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.93,0:02:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A servant of the Lord of Shioya.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.73,0:02:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.31,0:02:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you two, down below?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.14,0:02:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Genkei-sama, a great monk.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.35,0:03:04.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am Sougen, his servant and personal retainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.41,0:03:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My, my, a monk on my humble ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.66,0:03:13.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A monk at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.78,0:03:15.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.41,0:03:48.74,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The blue moon illuminated
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.79,0:03:52.71,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}your wandering shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.33,0:03:57.21,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I could never tell you all I wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.21,0:04:02.13,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,250)}It was so very frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.22,0:04:06.01,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I think about your faked smile,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.60,0:04:10.64,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}and forget all the hot tears we shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.10,0:04:13.31,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}What do these empty husks,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.35,0:04:19.15,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}those empty eyes of yours, reflect, my dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.90,0:04:24.36,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The transient quarter moon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.74,0:04:26.53,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,100)}hides in a rift in the clouds,
Dialogue: 1,0:04:26.49,0:04:28.91,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(100,300)}as darkness seeps up from the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.95,0:04:33.37,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Tell me the truth, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.71,0:04:35.54,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Are you so despondent
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.62,0:04:40.00,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,0)}that you still sit alone, sighing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.46,0:04:42.51,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}The First Night
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.68,0:04:49.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, this is an unusual ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.76,0:04:51.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve never seen a ship with a pond on the deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m glad you find it interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.27,0:04:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s my personal collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.69,0:05:01.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll show you the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.70,0:05:07.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What huge goldfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.03,0:05:12.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? This is the best aquarium in all the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.54,0:05:16.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many are there in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.42,0:05:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think that—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.71,0:05:19.34,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems we missed a passenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.34,0:05:21.63,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(640,619,640,690,200,0)\t(50,200,\c&HE9ECF1&\3c&H262B32&)}It seems we missed a passenger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:26.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s you, Mr. Medicine Seller!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.05,0:05:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He’s the one who exorcised the Ghost Cat from my home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.81,0:05:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A wind…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.89,0:05:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you a sorcerer as well, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.02,0:05:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a{\alpha&HFF&} medicine seller, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.40,0:05:42.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a medicine seller,{\alpha&HFF&} you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.73,0:05:45.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just a medicine seller, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.41,0:05:52.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the wind stays with us, we\Nshould be in Edo in four or five days.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.41,0:05:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Goromaru?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.08,0:05:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.58,0:05:59.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No stars tonight, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:02.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well, we don’t really need the stars to get our bearings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.09,0:06:10.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The compass points due north, so if we just\Nhead to the Northeast, we’ll reach Edo just fine.{}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.22,0:06:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Northeast, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.73,0:06:23.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If an Ayakashi or something shows up again, will you\Nkill it with your Sword of Exorcism, Mr. Medicine Seller?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.82,0:06:24.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.86,0:06:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.86,0:06:28.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.07,0:06:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,An Ayakashi is something that simply should not exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.62,0:06:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And yet, there are millions of Ayakashi, all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.62,0:06:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I could try to kill them all if I\Nwanted, but I would never get them all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.46,0:06:43.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Isn’t that what they say about Gods?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.71,0:06:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s similar.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.38,0:06:49.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s not true of Mononoke, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.36,0:07:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That Sword of Exorcism, would you\Nbe able to draw it, and show it to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.87,0:07:17.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I cannot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.45,0:07:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to draw it, the Mononoke’s\NForm, Truth and Regret must be evident.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.09,0:07:30.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His power doesn’t seem terribly\Nimpressive, for someone who acts so mysteriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.38,0:07:31.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Myself, on the other ha—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.01,0:07:35.05,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}That Night
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.81,0:09:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wind{\alpha&HFF&} has stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.40,0:09:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The wind has stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.91,0:09:22.91,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}The Second Night
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.47,0:09:36.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.63,0:09:40.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you’re all up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.93,0:09:45.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was wondering where you’d got to!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.56,0:09:47.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.98,0:09:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you see…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.65,0:09:55.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though morning has dawned, the sun is nowhere to be found,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.61,0:10:01.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and yet, it is a bright, beautiful day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.24,0:10:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama, you should stay out of the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.24,0:10:03.24,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it’s morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.50,0:10:06.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let us go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.50,0:10:06.50,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Should we not be able to see the port of Irouzaki by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.50,0:10:08.42,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(640,618,640,690,200,0)\t(50,200,\c&HE9ECF1&\3c&H262B32&)}Should we not be able to see the port of Irouzaki by now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.42,0:10:10.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.21,0:10:14.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I can’t see it at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.05,0:10:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.47,0:10:26.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, this is Niijima,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.44,0:10:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and this is Nojimazaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.65,0:10:34.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.40,0:10:35.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.15,0:10:37.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen well!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.65,0:10:43.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have heard that the area between\NNiijima, Nojimazaki, and the island of Nanban
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.66,0:10:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is called the Dragon’s Triangle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.46,0:10:49.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Dragon’s—
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.41,0:10:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Triangle?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:10:55.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Correct!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.88,0:11:01.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyone caught in this area will\Nbe attacked by unnatural Ayakashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.93,0:11:07.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and never return home!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.98,0:11:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My God!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.56,0:11:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.98,0:11:17.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Ayakashi’s Sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:20.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A—Ayakashi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.20,0:11:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th—That can’t be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.07,0:11:23.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goromaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.12,0:11:26.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S—See? Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.66,0:11:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The needle is pointing directly north!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.80,0:11:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,True enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.72,0:11:47.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This iron rod is a magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.64,0:11:53.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,With this hidden near the compass,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.69,0:11:57.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,one can control the direction of the needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.36,0:11:57.48,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,An interesting trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.48,0:11:58.15,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(640,616,640,690,200,0)\t(50,200,\c&HE9ECF1&\3c&H262B32&)}An interesting trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.15,0:12:02.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—Who on Earth would do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.99,0:12:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means the culprit is on this ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.33,0:12:16.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drums!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.59,0:12:18.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.75,0:12:20.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.17,0:12:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ayakashi known as the Kokuu Taiko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.38,0:12:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A—A—A—Ayakashi?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.39,0:12:32.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Simply hearing the sound of drums\Nat sea does little harm to one’s person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.85,0:12:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunate indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.23,0:12:42.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the ghost ship had appeared, I\Ncould have exorcised and destroyed it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.72,0:13:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What on Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.45,0:13:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems we’ve been trapped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.38,0:13:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,M—My goodness!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.05,0:13:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama, this is nothing more\Nthan someone’s idea of a joke, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.89,0:13:52.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remain calm, Sougen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.10,0:13:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ayakashi prey on those weak of mind and soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.77,0:13:56.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y—Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.89,0:13:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.52,0:14:02.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is, without a doubt, the\NDragon’s Triangle! The Ayakashi’s Sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.02,0:14:03.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.65,0:14:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kayo-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.48,0:14:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.07,0:14:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Mr. Scales!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.78,0:14:11.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S—Scales?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.20,0:14:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, precisely, is to be weighed?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.04,0:14:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These scales determine distance, not weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.29,0:14:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Distance?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.29,0:14:20.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Distance to what?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To something not of this Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.48,0:14:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.19,0:14:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I—Is this the ghost ship the sailor’s ghost commands?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.65,0:14:46.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea it was so big!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whether we decide to kill it, or display\Nit in Edo, this will require a bit of finesse.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.66,0:14:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why don’t you try killing it with this Sword of Exorcism?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.67,0:15:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’d like to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.30,0:15:07.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H—He told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.34,0:15:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He needs the Form, Truth and Regret!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.55,0:15:13.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would say that the Form is taken care of.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.64,0:15:20.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.03,0:15:35.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ghost ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.58,0:15:38.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sword isn’t responding!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.33,0:15:41.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.37,0:15:43.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready your ladles!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.25,0:15:45.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would do no good at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.71,0:15:47.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you say that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.46,0:15:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Such sluggish movement is uncharacteristic of an Ayakashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.51,0:15:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, it has not requested our ladle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.93,0:15:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th—Then, what do those dead things want?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.06,0:16:00.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They’re saying they wish us to join them.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.68,0:16:02.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t want to become one of those things!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:04.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Owner!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.02,0:16:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gather all your stove’s ashes, and bring them to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.36,0:16:09.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ashes?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.61,0:16:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.99,0:16:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.90,0:16:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.90,0:16:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goromaru!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.45,0:16:15.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll help!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.58,0:16:21.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why ash, and not salt?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.79,0:16:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.91,0:16:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There is much salt in the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.38,0:16:28.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will not work on the ghost ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.05,0:16:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will this be enough, do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.10,0:16:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.90,0:16:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It didn’t do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.27,0:16:52.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Owner, where are the ropes I saw wound about the firewood?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.45,0:16:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were burned along with the firewood!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.49,0:16:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anything other than wood ash contaminates the powder…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.29,0:17:02.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It will not ward off the dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.95,0:17:04.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.83,0:17:05.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.00,0:17:09.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that won’t work, I’ll just cut them!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.46,0:17:14.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They are not alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.13,0:17:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A tool for killing will have no effect whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.31,0:17:24.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.53,0:17:41.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We’re floating!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.24,0:17:42.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My poor boat!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.74,0:17:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A—Ack!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.00,0:17:46.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Medicine Seller, please do something!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.87,0:17:49.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I suppose I am a medicine seller, still.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.46,0:17:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be so calm?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.22,0:17:58.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Drugs won’t work on the Ayakashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:01.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.05,0:18:03.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re a spiritualist of sorts, aren’t you, Genyousai-dono?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.60,0:18:06.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you perform an evil-warding prayer?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.39,0:18:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.77,0:18:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then please do.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.65,0:18:14.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This medicine may take a while to mix.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.20,0:18:27.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Ayakashi come to this world through the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.21,0:18:35.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These Ayakashi are so\Nnumerous, indeed, as to block out the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.59,0:18:40.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we’ve no hope of escaping this trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.30,0:18:45.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, light comes forth not solely from the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.10,0:18:48.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you open your eyes, you will be blinded.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.34,0:19:20.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ghost ship is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.43,0:19:23.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re no ordinary medicine seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.01,0:19:25.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not bad at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.14,0:19:28.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you, he’s simply amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.77,0:19:31.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Genkei-sama, we’re saved!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.06,0:19:35.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—What was that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.27,0:19:37.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like chains.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.49,0:19:39.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.74,0:19:41.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sea is not called the Ayakashi’s Sea for naught!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.36,0:19:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why did we have to come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.70,0:19:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.16,0:19:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who manipulated the compass\Nto send us to this wretched place?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.91,0:19:54.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s certain someone here did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.25,0:19:56.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It wasn’t one of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.29,0:20:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Genyousai-san, you said you wanted to gain\Na reputation as an exorcist by defeating Ayakashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.13,0:20:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mikuniya-san, maybe you wanted to make it\Ninto a tourist attraction, like those giant goldfish!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:14.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sasaki-sama, you wanted to see\Nthe Medicine Seller’s sword so badly!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really, don’t you want it for your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.82,0:20:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may cast all the aspersions you wish, but I am innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.61,0:20:26.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And Sougen-san, you disappeared last night, didn’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.95,0:20:32.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W—Well, I became seasick, and\Nmerely needed a bit of fresh air.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.25,0:20:37.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of us is above suspicion, other than the Medicine Seller.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.42,0:20:43.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What Ayakashi will appear next?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.22,0:20:46.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.76,0:20:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve used up all my gunpowder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:54.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We cannot use the same trick again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.19,0:20:59.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you enjoying yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.57,0:21:01.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can’t be.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.74,0:21:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.74,0:21:05.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, Medicine Seller?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.57,0:21:10.03,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}To be continued
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.91,0:21:19.42,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Without you, I just can’t smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.55,0:21:30.47,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I walk this banal town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.47,0:21:36.56,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}feeling such intense emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.10,0:21:42.94,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I know that if I could treasure them and live on,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.03,0:21:52.24,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I would need nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.91,0:22:00.42,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}The summer flowers that bloomed in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.42,0:22:06.72,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Come falling down, dancing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.80,0:22:10.05,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I can barely recall the night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.05,0:22:13.35,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}where they all came tumbling down,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.35,0:22:24.19,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}so what I can still recall is all the more precious.
